<div class="cc-onboarding" id="cc-onboarding">
    {{#unless setup_context}}
    <div class="cc-onboarding-header">
        <h2>Welcome to your Control Center</h2>
        <p>This is where you'll see live conversations, skill usage, and analytics. To get started, connect Claude to systemprompt.io by following the steps below for your preferred client.</p>
        <p class="cc-onboarding-guide-links">For a detailed walkthrough, see the <a href="/platform/connecting" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Phase 1: Connect Claude guide</a> or view your complete <a href="/admin/setup">Setup Guide</a>.</p>
    </div>
    {{/unless}}

    <div class="cc-onboarding-tabs">
        <button type="button" class="cc-onboarding-tab cc-onboarding-tab--active" data-onboard="cowork">Cowork (Claude Desktop)</button>
        <button type="button" class="cc-onboarding-tab" data-onboard="code">Claude Code</button>
        <button type="button" class="cc-onboarding-tab" data-onboard="web">claude.ai</button>
    </div>

    <div class="cc-onboarding-panel cc-onboarding-panel--active" id="onboard-cowork">
        <div class="cc-onboarding-notice">
            <strong>Note:</strong> Cowork marketplace sync requires an Anthropic Enterprise plan with a GitHub private repo. Individual users should use the plugin ZIP export below.
        </div>
        <div class="cc-onboarding-steps">
            <div class="cc-onboarding-step">
                <span class="cc-step-number">1</span>
                <div class="cc-step-content">
                    <h3>Whitelist systemprompt.io</h3>
                    <p>In Claude Desktop, go to <strong>Settings &rarr; Capabilities &rarr; Code execution and file creation</strong>. Enable <strong>Allow network egress</strong>, set domain allowlist to <strong>Package managers only</strong>, then add these domains:</p>
                    <table class="cc-onboarding-table">
                        <tr><th>Domain</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
                        <tr><td>systemprompt.io</td><td>Main API and dashboard</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>*.systemprompt.io</td><td>Tenant subdomains</td></tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-onboarding-step">
                <span class="cc-step-number">2</span>
                <div class="cc-step-content">
                    <h3>Add MCP connector</h3>
                    <p>In Claude Desktop, go to <strong>Settings &rarr; Connectors</strong>, click <strong>Add custom connector</strong>, enter name <strong>Skill manager</strong> and paste this URL:</p>
                    <div class="cc-onboarding-code">
                        <code>{{marketplace.mcp_url}}</code>
                        <button type="button" class="btn-copy" data-copy="{{marketplace.mcp_url}}">Copy</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-onboarding-step">
                <span class="cc-step-number">3</span>
                <div class="cc-step-content">
                    <h3>Add global instructions</h3>
                    <p>In Claude Desktop <strong>Settings &rarr; Cowork</strong>, paste this into the <strong>Global instructions</strong> field:</p>
                    <div class="cc-onboarding-code">
                        <code>We use systemprompt mcp skills to manage all skills, plugins and agents. Always use the MCP server for CRUD operations to ensure complete consistency.</code>
                        <button type="button" class="btn-copy" data-copy="We use systemprompt mcp skills to manage all skills, plugins and agents. Always use the MCP server for CRUD operations to ensure complete consistency.">Copy</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-onboarding-step">
                <span class="cc-step-number">4</span>
                <div class="cc-step-content">
                    <h3>Export &amp; import plugin</h3>
                    <p>Go to <a href="/admin/my/marketplace">My Marketplace</a> and click <strong>Export for Cowork</strong> to download your merged plugin ZIP. In Claude Desktop, go to <strong>Settings &rarr; Plugins &rarr; Import</strong> and upload the ZIP file. This single plugin contains all your skills, agents, and connectors.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-onboarding-step">
                <span class="cc-step-number">5</span>
                <div class="cc-step-content">
                    <h3>Run /onboarding</h3>
                    <p>Open Cowork, start a new conversation, and type <code>/onboarding</code>. The assistant will guide you through creating personalised skills for your business.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cc-onboarding-panel" id="onboard-code">
        <div class="cc-onboarding-notice">
            <strong>Note:</strong> Claude Code supports plugin import via ZIP or git-based marketplace sync with any git URL.
        </div>
        <div class="cc-onboarding-steps">
            <div class="cc-onboarding-step">
                <span class="cc-step-number">1</span>
                <div class="cc-step-content">
                    <h3>Whitelist systemprompt.io</h3>
                    <p>In Claude Desktop, go to <strong>Settings &rarr; Capabilities &rarr; Code execution and file creation</strong>. Enable <strong>Allow network egress</strong>, set domain allowlist to <strong>Package managers only</strong>, then add these domains:</p>
                    <table class="cc-onboarding-table">
                        <tr><th>Domain</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
                        <tr><td>systemprompt.io</td><td>Main API and dashboard</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>*.systemprompt.io</td><td>Tenant subdomains</td></tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-onboarding-step">
                <span class="cc-step-number">2</span>
                <div class="cc-step-content">
                    <h3>Add MCP connector</h3>
                    <p>In Claude Desktop, go to <strong>Settings &rarr; Connectors</strong>, click <strong>Add custom connector</strong>, enter name <strong>Skill manager</strong> and paste this URL:</p>
                    <div class="cc-onboarding-code">
                        <code>{{marketplace.mcp_url}}</code>
                        <button type="button" class="btn-copy" data-copy="{{marketplace.mcp_url}}">Copy</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-onboarding-step">
                <span class="cc-step-number">3</span>
                <div class="cc-step-content">
                    <h3>Export &amp; import plugin</h3>
                    <p>Go to <a href="/admin/my/marketplace">My Marketplace</a> and click <strong>Export for Cowork</strong> to download your merged plugin ZIP. In Claude Code, run <code>/plugin install /path/to/exported.zip</code> to import the plugin.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-onboarding-step">
                <span class="cc-step-number">4</span>
                <div class="cc-step-content">
                    <h3>Connect the plugin</h3>
                    <p>After installing, go to <strong>Customize &rarr; Personal plugins &rarr; Systemprompt &rarr; Connectors</strong>, find the skill manager connector, and click <strong>Connect</strong>. Your skills, agents, and tools will then be available &mdash; events will appear here automatically.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cc-onboarding-panel" id="onboard-web">
        <div class="cc-onboarding-steps">
            <div class="cc-onboarding-step">
                <span class="cc-step-number">1</span>
                <div class="cc-step-content">
                    <h3>Add remote MCP integration</h3>
                    <p>On <strong>claude.ai</strong>, go to <strong>Settings &rarr; Integrations</strong> and click <strong>Add more</strong>. Enter this URL as a custom integration:</p>
                    <div class="cc-onboarding-code">
                        <code>{{marketplace.mcp_url}}</code>
                        <button type="button" class="btn-copy" data-copy="{{marketplace.mcp_url}}">Copy</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-onboarding-step">
                <span class="cc-step-number">2</span>
                <div class="cc-step-content">
                    <h3>Authorize and use</h3>
                    <p>When prompted, authorize with your systemprompt.io account. Your skills, agents, and tools will then be available in claude.ai conversations. Events will appear here automatically.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>